Author: Kouki Ooyatsu <kouki-o@iij.ad.jp>
Date:   Mon Jan 21 17:22:18 2013 +0900

    Fix uninitialized variable in hex_to_str().
    
     * In the worst case cause a Segmentation Fault
       * VM read the irep is illegal irep code.
    
     * Because, since it's not NULL terminated in the process of strncpy(3),
       it may strtol(3) doesn't return the correct value.

commit e2ad91855efe4ca12da00fa4278f55cde57c6ec6
Author: Kouki Ooyatsu <kouki-o@iij.ad.jp>
Date:   Mon Jan 21 17:22:18 2013 +0900

    Fix uninitialized variable in hex_to_str().
    
     * In the worst case cause a Segmentation Fault
       * VM read the irep is illegal irep code.
    
     * Because, since it's not NULL terminated in the process of strncpy(3),
       it may strtol(3) doesn't return the correct value.

diff --git a/src/load.c b/src/load.c
index 4ac6952..911dbd6 100644
--- a/src/load.c
+++ b/src/load.c
@@ -727,6 +727,8 @@ hex_to_str(char *hex, char *str, uint16_t *str_len)
       case '\?': /* fall through */
       case '\\': *dst++ = *src; break;
       default:
+        memset(buf, 0x00, sizeof(buf));
+
         if (*src >= '0' && *src <= '7') {
           base = 8;
           strncpy(buf, src, 3);
